               stealing, on the <rs id="t18250630-117-cd591" type="crimeDate">24th of June</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250630-117-off590 t18250630-117-cd591"></join>, a night cap, value 6 d.; a sheet, value 1 s., and seven yards of linen, value 8 s. 6 d.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               <persName id="t18250630-117-victim615" type="victimName">
                  Catherine 
                  Shepherd
               <interp inst="t18250630-117-victim615" type="surname" value="Shepherd"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250630-117-victim615" type="given" value="Catherine"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250630-117-victim615" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250630-117-off590 t18250630-117-victim615"></join>
                  </persName>
            , <rs id="t18250630-117-viclabel592" type="occupation">widow</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250630-117-victim615 t18250630-117-viclabel592"></join>.</p>
               <p>CATHERINE SHEPHERD. I <rs id="t18250630-117-viclabel593" type="occupation">keep the <placeName id="t18250630-117-crimeloc594">Wheatsheaf public-house, in West Smithfield</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t18250630-117-crimeloc594" type="placeName" value="Wheatsheaf public-house, in West Smithfield"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250630-117-crimeloc594" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250630-117-off590 t18250630-117-crimeloc594"></join>
                  </rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250630-117-victim615 t18250630-117-viclabel593"></join>. On the night of the 24th of June, I was sitting in my parlour, and saw the prisoner come down stairs, and go out at the door; I ran down Hosier-lane after him; my boy was with me - I left him to pursue, and I went back. The prisoner was taken to the watch-house, and the linen was brought to me directly; it is mine: it had been part in the club-room, and part in the kitchen.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250630-117-person616">
                  WILLIAM 
                  DARBY
               <interp inst="t18250630-117-person616" type="surname" value="DARBY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250630-117-person616" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250630-117-person616" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the waiter. I pursued the prisoner, and cried Stop thief! he struck at me with an umbrella, and then fell down. I did not lose sight of him till he was secured; this bundle was found in his hat; he dropped the sheet in Hosier-lane: it had been wrapped round his body.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250630-117-person617">
                  JOHN 
                  M'DONALD
               <interp inst="t18250630-117-person617" type="surname" value="M'DONALD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250630-117-person617" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250630-117-person617" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I saw the prisoner running down Hosier-lane, and then into Foxenall-court - when I came up he was endeavouring to unbutton<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182506300039"></xptr>his trowsers - I found some linen in his trowsers; I did not search his hat.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was quite insensible - I was not even able to tell my name, or where I lived; all I was able to say, was,</p>
               <p>"Give me a drink of water."</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18250630-117-verdict595" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18250630-117-verdict595" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 37.</p>
